# SvelteKit Patterns

- Use SvelteKit-native patterns first:
  - `+page.server.ts` for server-side data loading and form actions.
  - `+page.ts` only for safe public client-side loading.
  - `+layout.server.ts` for shared authenticated server data.
  - `hooks.server.ts` for session/auth bootstrapping.
- Prefer server-first data access for anything sensitive.
- Do not fetch Supabase directly from the client unless the data is explicitly safe under RLS and intended for public/client use.
- Keep secrets and privileged logic out of `+page.ts`, `+layout.ts`, and client components.
- Use form actions for mutations when appropriate instead of ad hoc client fetch calls.
- When adding endpoints, use SvelteKit request handlers with explicit validation and auth checks.
- Avoid unnecessary stores if load functions or props are sufficient.
- Keep page data serializable and minimal.

## Svelte Components

- Keep components focused and presentational where possible.
- Move sensitive logic and data writes out of components into server files/actions/endpoints.
- Do not put direct privileged Supabase logic into client components.
- Use reactive statements sparingly and clearly.
- Avoid unnecessary global stores.
- Preserve accessibility: label inputs, use buttons for actions, keep keyboard navigation intact, do not break focus behavior.
